\f1\b \ul LAND-BASED TRADE
\f0\b0 \ulnone \
\
The Ring and its major conduits are the heart of trade, commerce within the Lands. The role of the Riders in protecting the roads makes them crucial to its success and explains why they are closely tied into various commercial Guilds. \
\
Major guilds manage what we would think of as \'93stores\'94.  Most towns host regular \'93fairs\'94, on various schedules, and support open-air bazaars for small dealers and individuals. \
\
\

\f1\b \ul RIVER-BASED TRADE
\f0\b0 \ulnone \
\
As important as movement of goods on the Ring roads is movement of goods on the rivers and their tributaries. Here the eastern communes in Eibar and Nye Lands and Biver have a bigger influence, as they tend to have the best capacities for maintaining fleets on the rivers, as well as handling sea-borne imports and exports.\
\
\

\f1\b \ul SEA-GOING TRADE
\f0\b0 \ulnone \
\
In the larger context, sea-going trade in the near-sea is dominated by huum from Saskan Lands and animals or mixed sentients from both Ilyushan and Krbshanana, with some from the Forgh, the Komikol and Aranzen. \
\
Except for Ilyushan, the regions which border the Heliopticon to the East and to the South have enormous coastlines.  In the case of Krbshanana, it also has a large sentient marine population living 
\f2\i within
\f0\i0  the Krbsh Sea itself. \
\
While we learn about lands further afield, outside the Enclosure, they don\'92t play an important role in the economy of the Saskan Lands.\
